<h1>User Guidelines</h1>

<p>We created this User Guidelines so you can help us protect this great car loving

community.</p>

<p>By using Kar Page, you agree to these guidelines and our Terms of Use. Violating these boundaries set herein, may result in deleted content, disabled accounts, or other restrictions.</p>
<p><strong>Share only photos and videos that you’ve taken or have the right to share.</strong> As always, you own the content you post on Kar Page. Remember to post authentic content, and don’t post anything that you don’t have the right to post.</p>
<p><strong>Post photos and videos that are appropriate for the Kar Page community

and audience.</strong> We don’t allow nudity on Kar Page. This includes photos, videos,

and some digitally-created content that show sexual intercourse or genitals. If

you share photos or videos of children, for safety reasons, we may remove

images that show nude or partially-nude children. Even when this content is

shared with good intentions, it could be used by others in unanticipated ways.
</p>
<p><strong>Help us stay spam-free</strong> by not collecting artificial likes and followers, or posting

repetitive comments or content, or repeatedly contacting people for commercial

purposes without their consent.</p>

<p><strong>Always follow the law</strong>. Kar Page is not a place to support or praise terrorism,

organized crime, or hate groups. Offering sexual services, buying or selling

firearms and illegal or prescription drugs (even if it’s legal in your region), and

promoting online gambling are absolutely NOT allowed. We have zero tolerance

when it comes to sharing sexual content involving minors.
</p>
<p><strong>Respect all members of the Kar Page community</strong>. We want a positive

community. We remove content that contains credible threats or hate speech,

content that targets private individuals to degrade or shame them, personal

information meant to blackmail or harass someone. It's NEVER OK to encourage

violence or attack anyone based on their race, ethnicity, national origin, sex,

gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, religious affiliation, disabilities, or

diseases. Serious threats of harm to public and personal safety are NOT allowed.

We carefully review all reports and consider many things when determining

whether a threat is credible.
</p>
<p><strong>Newsworthy events.</strong> If you use Kar Page to share important and newsworthy

events. Sharing graphic images, or videos of intense, graphic violence, or

content for sadistic pleasure or to glorify violence is NEVER allowed, and it will

be removed to make sure Kar Page stays appropriate place for the car loving

community. We may work with law enforcement, including when we believe that

there’s risk of physical harm or threat to public safety.</p>

<p><strong>We all are an important part of the Kar Page community</strong>, so if you see

something that you think may violate our guidelines, please report it by using our

built-in reporting options. We have a team that always reviews these reports and

works as quickly as possible to remove content that doesn’t meet our guidelines.
</p>
<p>When you report, please try to provide as much information as possible, such as

links, usernames, and descriptions of the content, so we can find and review it

quickly. We may remove entire posts if either the imagery or associated captions

violate our guidelines.
</p>
<p>-You may find content you don’t like, but doesn’t violate the User Guidelines. If

that happens, you can <strong>unfollow</strong> or <strong>block</strong> the person who posted it. If there's

something you don't like in a comment on one of your posts, you can delete that

comment.
</p>
<p>-Many disagreements and misunderstandings can be resolved directly between

members of the community. If one of your photos or videos was posted by

someone else, you could try commenting on the post and asking the person to

take it down. If that doesn’t work, you can report that content, and we will review

it as quickly as possible. If you believe someone is violating your trademark and

copyrights, you can report that profile from the built-in reporting option inside of

their profile.
</p>
